verbs.description: preservatize (third-person singular simple present preservatizes, present participle preservatizing, simple past and past participle preservatized)

entries.meaning: (transitive, chiefly Australia, New Zealand) To treat with a preservative.
examples: Mr. Law states:— "The writer of the paragraph endeavors to give the impression that most of the fish being sold in Perth is preservatised, and as it is spoken of as reeking of preservatives, it is assumed that chemical preservatives are suggested.  […] "
